<L>__{interior hallway day}
<A>__{tenzin gyatso peeks through a door at the great assembly. the lord chamberlian stands behind him.}
<L>__{interior great hall day}
<A>__{the layman continues.}
<C>__{layman}
<D>__{our treasuries are empty. our army is depleted. he would have us pull the hair from our noses.}
<L>__{interior hallway day}
<A>__{the dalai lama is confused, but continues listening.}
<L>__{interior great hall day}
<A>__{the layman returns to his cross legged position. the senior monk speaks.}
<C>__{monk}
<D>__{we note this. now, the chinese.}
<A>__{there is audible expression of tension.}
<C>__{monk}
<D>__{the allies wish to build a supply road from india, crossing tibet, as part of their war effort. the road would lead directly to china.}
<A>__{the layman gets to his knees.}
<C>__{layman}
<D>__{we cannot allow it. right now, we have a only a small chinese mission in lhasa, the first since the thirteenth dalai lama threw them out in 1912. the road would increase the size of that mission. the chinese would try to control our trade, as they did once before, control our contact with the outside world.}
